Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["scaling studies ", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981808129315954*^9, 
  3.9818081319025855`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b5c9a82e-0442-4e7f-9cb6-\
bbd4ab0aae40"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["the analytic handles on scaling of microphysics parameters", \
"Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.98180849941317*^9, 
  3.98180850748218*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"81aa7c88-d075-4e89-99b4-\
fc417ba19dfb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "we want to understand the scaling with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "D"], ",", 
    FractionBox[
     SubscriptBox["m", 
      SubscriptBox["e", "D"]], 
     SubscriptBox["m", 
      SubscriptBox["p", "D"]]], ",", 
    SubscriptBox["f", "D"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "72f0e948-86cc-40e2-9232-9e616e4a30eb"],
 ". \n-For fixed \[Kappa], we have that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["f", "D"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "f5ed5b48-a7f0-41c3-8cb4-1a8bcb413753"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Alpha]", "D"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "1b437743-7925-4ded-8eb2-373870a3dcfa"],
 " only appear non-linearly in the debye momentum of the plasma ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox["z", "D"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "0714f67e-28d7-4bd5-8fe6-af2fc24f135b"],
 "), The handle we have is that everywhere we are interested in has ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["z", "D"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "38c4885e-9761-4a6f-a6d6-334115c14cce"],
 " as the smallest parameter in the problem so we can expand and see the \
scaling. \n\n-For the mass ratio, it should only appear in the kinematic \
function. And I suspect that it can also be shown to not significantly change \
things, in all cases the ratio will either be large small or 1 for each of \
the rate contributions, so we should be able to predict the scaling"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9818081341835938`*^9, 3.9818081886861987`*^9}, {
  3.981808218855136*^9, 3.9818083019846478`*^9}, {3.981808417050109*^9, 
  3.981808489584166*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"37da14a3-04ca-4947-99e5-\
f12152a1bff3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

